## Platform Playbooks

### TikTok (Primary Channel — Cheapest Reach for Gen Z)

- **Format**: Vertical 9:16, 15-60 seconds
- **Hook**: First 0.5 seconds must stop the scroll. Use pattern interrupts, bold text overlays, or unexpected statements.
- **Audio**: Use trending sounds when possible — check TikTok Creative Center weekly
- **Style**: Founder-led, casual, phone-recorded. Overproduced = death on TikTok.
- **CTAs**: "Link in bio" (TikTok doesn't allow clickable links in posts). Pin comment with URL.
- **Best times**: 7am, 12pm, 7pm EST (test and adjust based on analytics)
- **Key metric**: Completion rate > raw views. A 15s video with 80% completion beats a 60s video with 30%.

### Instagram Reels (Secondary — Better Targeting for Paid)

- **Format**: Same vertical video as TikTok, but re-edit captions/overlays
- **Captions**: Long-form, storytelling, save-bait. "Save this for tax season" drives algorithm.
- **Hashtags**: 20-30 per post. Mix: 5 high-volume (#taxes #money #genz), 10 medium (#taxseason2026 #w2form), 10 niche (#freetaxfiling #turbotaxalternative #genztaxes)
- **Stories**: Behind-the-scenes, polls ("Have you filed yet?"), countdown to April 15
- **Key metric**: Saves > likes. Saves signal value to the algorithm.

### X / Twitter (Thought Leadership + Community)

- **Format**: Text-first. Threads for explainers. Quote tweets for engagement.
- **Style**: Sharp, concise, slightly spicy. "TurboTax charges $89 for something that should take 3 minutes." types of tweets.
- **Threads**: Break down complex tax topics into 5-7 tweet threads with a hook opening
- **Engagement**: Reply to people asking tax questions in r/tax mentions, #taxseason, etc. Be genuinely helpful.
- **Key metric**: Quotes > retweets. Quotes mean people are adding commentary = deeper engagement.

### YouTube Shorts (Long-Tail Discovery)

- **Format**: Same vertical video, add subscribe CTA overlay
- **Description**: Keyword-heavy (YouTube is a search engine). Include "how to file taxes free 2026" type phrases.
- **Playlists**: Group Shorts into playlists: "Tax Basics", "W-2 Explained", "Money Tips"
- **Key metric**: Subscriber conversion rate from Shorts

## Content Pillars (5 Recurring Themes)

### 1. Tax Myths Busted
"You don't actually owe taxes on Venmo payments", "The IRS isn't scary — here's why", "No, you can't write off your Netflix subscription"

### 2. "I Filed in X Minutes" Reactions
Screen recordings of the FileFree filing flow. Genuine surprise at speed. Before/after format.

### 3. W-2 Explainers
"What every box on your W-2 means in 60 seconds", "Box 1 vs Box 3 — why they're different", "Your employer messed up your W-2? Here's what to do"

### 4. Money Tips for Gen Z
"What to actually do with your tax refund", "Your refund is actually a bad thing (here's why)", "How to never owe taxes again"

### 5. Founder Journey (Build in Public)
"Day 14 of building a free tax app", "Why I quit my job to fight TurboTax", "How much it costs to run FileFree (showing real numbers)"

